author: Ravi Amblee
text: It is heartbreaking to see Indian workers physically doing all the hard work, that is not only killing their learning age but also killing the opportunities to become better skilled and earn more. They do all the hard work and go back to the same dungeon dens. When will their standard of living going to improve if they do manual dudgery work all thru their life? We are keeping them as manual workers for generations. To win the global race, India need to train workers to use robots and Artificial Intelligence. Although solar is important, but how we build it matters.Why there are no robots of any kind in this project? This is where India is losing its race against developed world. If we use robots, not only workers get paid high, the cost of project will come down, the projects pace increases and multiple projects can be done simultaneously creating more skilled jobs. If Artificial intelligence is used to augment robots, no one can beat India. I think companies like Adani must start using robots and AI and at the same time train the employees to enhance their skills.
